 About 63,487 shares traded. Ares Dynamic Credit Allocation Fund, Inc. (ARDC) has 0.00% since July 20, 2016 and is . It has underperformed by 16.70% the S&P500.







Among 31 analysts covering Parsley Energy Inc (NYSE:PE), 26 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 5 Hold. Therefore 84% are positive. Parsley Energy Inc has $48 highest and $16 lowest target. $33.10’s average target is 16.18% above currents $28.49 stock price. Parsley Energy Inc had 75 analyst reports since July 21, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The rating was maintained by RBC Capital Markets with “Sector Perform” on Friday, November 6. Barclays Capital maintained it with “Overweight” rating and $41 target in Friday, February 10 report. The rating was initiated by Barclays Capital on Tuesday, June 21 with “Overweight”. The rating was downgraded by Macquarie Research on Wednesday, October 12 to “Neutral”. The company was initiated on Wednesday, December 2 by Deutsche Bank. UBS maintained the shares of PE in report on Thursday, August 4 with “Buy” rating. The rating was maintained by Topeka Capital Markets on Thursday, February 25 with “Buy”. The firm has “Buy” rating by Nomura given on Thursday, December 3. The stock of Parsley Energy Inc (NYSE:PE) has “Market Perform” rating given on Tuesday, April 5 by Cowen & Co. The company was maintained on Monday, July 17 by Northland Capital.
